To navigate to the “Catalog Definitions > Maintain Items” module, first I need to open the Application Navigator by clicking the “All” button in the top bar. click('79') ## step 1 To navigate to the Service Catalog application modules, click on “Service Catalog” in the All menu. click('294') ## step 2 To get directly to the “Maintain Items” list, navigate to its module via URL. This should open the sc_cat_item list where we can sort the columns. goto("https://dev226733.service-now.com/nav_to.do?uri=%2Fcom.glideapp.servicecatalog_cat_item_list.do") ## step 3 The current URL within the iframe is showing a page-not-found error. To navigate to the “Catalog Definitions > Maintain Items” module, I will use the global application navigator search. First, I'll click the top‐level search combobox with bid "113". click('113') ## step 4 I need to search for the “Maintain Items” module in the Application Navigator. I will type “Maintain Items” into the search box to find it. fill('113', 'Maintain Items') ## step 5 I need to execute the search for the "Maintain Items" module by pressing Enter on the search field to open the module. press('113', 'Enter') ## step 6 To access the “Maintain Items” module in the Application Navigator instead of the global search, I need to change the search context.
